{
  "texts": [
    "Safety considerations from advanced monitoringTurchin considers use of AI to monitor AI [92]: \"To be able to understand what is going on inside the main AI, we may need another AI.",
    "Below there are several ideas about how it could be implemented:• Narrow AI system to detect abnormalities in AI behavior …: It could test the consistency of its modules, run quick technical tests etc.",
    "Relatively simple neural net could overview main patterns in data flows of the main AI and recognize when they will change.",
    "Obviously, it should be protected from access by the main AI, and maybe even hardcoded in the remote hardware.",
    "• AGI to judge behavior of another, more powerful AI.For example, a human upload may judge actions of a more complex system."
  ]
}